					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Diane Wilson</h4>
												<p>Diane Wilson is a Dakota writer, educator, and bog steward, enrolled on the Rosebud Reservation. She has published six award-winning books as well as essays in numerous publications. Her novel, <i>The Seed Keeper</i>, won the 2022 MN Book Award and is a selection for the 2026 NEA Big Read. Wilson’s work explores seed sovereignty, social justice, cultural recovery, and environmental stewardship. She is currently working on a memoir, <i>Mapping My Way Home: A Story of Love, Loss, and a Bog.</i></p>
